# 4.6 Six Thinking Hats

## Blue Hat — Process

> Identify the company’s funding needs.
> Find a suitable online investment platform.
> Prepare and upload company information.
> Contact investors and arrange presentations.
> Review investor feedback and follow up.

## Red Hat — Feelings

> Jia Hui feels worried about the company’s financial problems.
> She feels nervous when presenting to foreign investors.
> She may feel disappointed if investors reject her idea.
> Successful investment can make her feel confident and hopeful.

## Yellow Hat — Benefits

> Foreign investment can improve the company’s cash flow.
> The company can hire more skilled employees.
> More funding can support product development.
> Foreign investors may provide international business connections.
> The online platform makes it easier to find suitable investors.

## White Hat — Facts and Information

> Jia Hui’s company has limited cash flow.
> The company needs funding for employees and business development.
> Investors need clear financial data and a growth plan.
> Jia Hui must upload an accurate company profile.
> A clear business presentation can help investors understand the company.

## Black Hat — Risks and Problems

> Investors may reject the business proposal.
> Jia Hui may need to give away part of the company’s ownership.
> Some online investors may not be reliable.
> Financial and company information may have privacy risks.
> Language and cultural differences may cause communication problems.

## Green Hat — Creative Ideas

> Create a bilingual company profile.
> Add a short product demonstration video.
> Use AI to match the company with suitable foreign investors.
> Provide an online meeting and presentation function.
> Add investor verification to improve trust.
> Include automatic translation for messages and documents.

## Most Important Observations

